A circuit breaker does NOT protect Callers.
It protects the service itself from
Dependency meltdown
Thread pool exhaustion
Connection pool exhaustion
Cascading failures


🎯 When You DO NOT Need Circuit Breaker

You probably don't need it if ALL of these are true:

Script runs rarely

Script makes 1 call at a time

No concurrency

GitLab failures are rare

Service has low load

No other future consumers expected

🚨 When You STILL Need Circuit Breaker (Even With 1 Script)

You should use it if:

Script runs in a loop (100+ calls)

Script runs concurrently

Multiple pipelines triggered in parallel

GitLab sometimes rate-limits (429)

Your service uses threads/workers

You want fast-fail behavior

You want to avoid retry storm
